1055
01:10:42,520 --> 01:10:44,639
- making passes at all the nurses...
- (PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1056
01:10:44,640 --> 01:10:49,039
and he told me to tell all of
you he has a terrific idea...

1057
01:10:49,040 --> 01:10:52,479
- for a new hospital number.
- Hold it, Audrey!

1058
01:10:52,480 --> 01:10:55,039
Hospital number, hospital number!

1059
01:10:55,040 --> 01:10:58,239
Just give me a minute. Stan,
will you give me some room?

1060
01:10:58,240 --> 01:11:01,399
- How does the title "Hospital Hop" grab you?
- It grabs me.

1061
01:11:01,400 --> 01:11:03,648
- Great, great.
- (♪ JAUNTY PIANO)

1062
01:11:05,600 --> 01:11:09,039
- I think I got it. I got it!
- I think he's got it!

1063
01:11:09,040 --> 01:11:11,519
Stan, help me out, please.

1064
01:11:11,520 --> 01:11:14,326
Clap your hands!

1065
01:11:19,240 --> 01:11:21,919
- Cheer up!
- (CLAPPING CONTINUES)

1066
01:11:21,920 --> 01:11:24,487
Let's go! Everybody!

1067
01:11:34,760 --> 01:11:36,919
- (♪ ENDS)
- (JONESY) And Lucas...

1068
01:11:36,920 --> 01:11:39,599
they are without question
an absolutely...

1069
01:11:39,600 --> 01:11:41,639
marvelous cast.

1070
01:11:41,640 --> 01:11:44,839
Now we gotta wait around
four months.

1071
01:11:44,840 --> 01:11:46,999
Maybe even lose them.

1072
01:11:47,000 --> 01:11:51,039
I can see where it'd be difficult
to hold a cast like that together.

1073
01:11:51,040 --> 01:11:53,479
It's really a shame.

1074
01:11:53,480 --> 01:11:56,199
And, of course,
even after four months...

1075
01:11:56,200 --> 01:11:58,839
a heart attack... (CHUCKLING)

1076
01:11:58,840 --> 01:12:01,679
There's no guarantee
that he'll be able to work.

1077
01:12:01,680 --> 01:12:03,639
None.

1078
01:12:03,640 --> 01:12:06,366
Jules, it's still too bright.

1079
01:12:07,840 --> 01:12:11,079
- Take number seven down to five...
- And he's the greatest.

1080
01:12:11,080 --> 01:12:13,328
- And eight down to two.
- Hmm.

1081
01:12:14,600 --> 01:12:18,639
And Lucas,
I think we have a sure hit.

1082
01:12:18,640 --> 01:12:21,079
A sure hit.

1083
01:12:21,080 --> 01:12:23,044
Reads like a dream.

1084
01:12:24,400 --> 01:12:26,799
I'd love to read it sometime.

1085
01:12:26,800 --> 01:12:29,679
I'll get a copy to you
this afternoon.

1086
01:12:29,680 --> 01:12:32,724
(CHUCKLING)
Oh, I forgot. Wait a minute.

1087
01:12:34,320 --> 01:12:38,159
- I've got one right here with me.
- (BOTH CHUCKLING)

1088
01:12:38,160 --> 01:12:40,567
Dimmer five up to three.

1089
01:12:41,440 --> 01:12:43,479
Hold that. That's good.

1090
01:12:43,480 --> 01:12:46,279
I know you couldn't care less
about the money.

1091
01:12:46,280 --> 01:12:50,199
- Hmm?
- What do you think about this, Lucas?

1092
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:52,402
Is it any better?

1093
01:12:53,440 --> 01:12:57,879
No. No, no.
It needs to be more... shadowy.

1094
01:12:57,880 --> 01:12:59,999
We talked about this, Jules.

1095
01:13:00,000 --> 01:13:02,239
It's a seduction scene.

1096
01:13:02,240 --> 01:13:05,091
Take the shadow lights to half.

1097
01:13:06,280 --> 01:13:09,999
How much, uh... is Joe getting?

1098
01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:13,239
Five percent of the gross
until payoff.

1099
01:13:13,240 --> 01:13:16,799
Then he goes to six percent. Twenty
percent of subsidiary rights...

1100
01:13:16,800 --> 01:13:20,083
- including a movie sale.
- (JULES) Thanks. That's good.

1101
01:13:23,160 --> 01:13:26,079
(EXHALES FORCEFULLY) Well...

1102
01:13:26,080 --> 01:13:29,409
of course my schedule's
impossible, but, uh...

1103
01:13:33,600 --> 01:13:37,319
you know how I feel
about you, Jonesy.

1104
01:13:37,320 --> 01:13:39,399
You've been like a father to me.

1105
01:13:39,400 --> 01:13:41,967
And you a son to me.

1106
01:13:43,200 --> 01:13:45,999
(JOE) I always look for
the worst in people.

1107
01:13:46,000 --> 01:13:47,919
A piece of you in them?

1108
01:13:47,920 --> 01:13:50,479
Yeah. A piece of me.

1109
01:13:50,480 --> 01:13:52,599
And generally, I find it.

1110
01:13:52,600 --> 01:13:56,439
Well, it may take you years,
but you'll find it.

1111
01:13:56,440 --> 01:13:59,962
(GIGGLES)
Oh, you're cute. You are cute.

1112
01:14:07,440 --> 01:14:09,599
It's looking better.

1113
01:14:09,600 --> 01:14:12,759
I think we'll move you upstairs
to a private room.

1114
01:14:12,760 --> 01:14:14,959
Oh, yeah.

1115
01:14:14,960 --> 01:14:18,559
But you better rest. If you
don't, you're in for trouble.

1116
01:14:18,560 --> 01:14:21,799
Oh, I will, Doctor.

1117
01:14:21,800 --> 01:14:25,971
I promise. I will.

1118
01:14:26,000 --> 01:14:28,407
- (♪ ROCK)
- (NO AUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

1119
01:14:40,960 --> 01:14:42,924
Mr. Gideon!

1120
01:14:51,120 --> 01:14:53,399
Mr. Gideon, what are you doing?

1121
01:14:53,400 --> 01:14:56,759
Oh, this?
I was just getting rid of it.

1122
01:14:56,760 --> 01:15:00,279
I caught someone smoking and told
him a man in my condition...

1123
01:15:00,280 --> 01:15:02,479
shouldn't even be around smoke.

1124
01:15:02,480 --> 01:15:04,444
(♪ UP-TEMPO)

1125
01:15:10,960 --> 01:15:14,199
I'm telling you, Gideon,
I got real insight into you.

1126
01:15:14,200 --> 01:15:17,039
There's a deep-rooted fear
of being conventional.

1127
01:15:17,040 --> 01:15:19,083
Right.

1128
01:15:25,040 --> 01:15:27,359
Your blood pressure
is higher than we hoped.

1129
01:15:27,360 --> 01:15:29,359
Your cardiograms
haven't improved one bit.

1130
01:15:29,360 --> 01:15:32,564
If you don't give a damn,
it's hard to expect us to.

1131
01:15:41,960 --> 01:15:43,969
Mr. Gideon!

1132
01:15:45,760 --> 01:15:48,079
I'll leave these menus with you.

1133
01:15:48,080 --> 01:15:51,279
Please check off what you want
for the coming weeks, okay?

1134
01:15:51,280 --> 01:15:55,399
Monday, I'll have roast beef. Tuesday,
chicken. Wednesday, steak.

1135
01:15:55,400 --> 01:15:59,519
Thursday I plan to be dead, so...
I'll just have something light.

1136
01:15:59,520 --> 01:16:01,210
Mr. Gideon!

1137
01:16:03,440 --> 01:16:05,642
(♪ CONTINUES)

1138
01:16:07,240 --> 01:16:11,119
She wrote a little note on the back.
She said you'd understand.

1139
01:16:11,120 --> 01:16:13,999
"Dear loving, giving, generous"...

1140
01:16:14,000 --> 01:16:16,559
underlined four times... "Dad...

1141
01:16:16,560 --> 01:16:20,759
I hear nurses are nice people.
Hint, hint.

1142
01:16:20,760 --> 01:16:24,439
Your poor, brother-less daughter."

1143
01:16:24,440 --> 01:16:27,007
Joe, what does it mean?

1144
01:16:28,160 --> 01:16:30,959
It means she's inherited
her mother's determination.

1145
01:16:30,960 --> 01:16:33,039
That's what it means.

1146
01:16:33,040 --> 01:16:36,289
(♪ SCATTING)

1147
01:16:39,880 --> 01:16:42,208
- (♪ ENDS)
- (AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

1148
01:16:43,440 --> 01:16:45,999
(MAN LAUGHING)

1149
01:16:46,000 --> 01:16:49,119
Oh, no. Thank you. No, no, no, no.

1150
01:16:49,120 --> 01:16:52,399
You're wonderful, wonderful.
The word "superstar"...

1151
01:16:52,400 --> 01:16:54,599
is greatly overused
in this business.

1152
01:16:54,600 --> 01:16:56,359
- Mm.
- But for my next guest...

1153
01:16:56,360 --> 01:16:59,079
the word "superstar"
is totally inadequate.

1154
01:16:59,080 --> 01:17:03,599
Whenever I do a benefit... and I've
done 150, 160, 170 this year...

1155
01:17:03,600 --> 01:17:07,639
all for very worthy causes...
I can always count on this dude...

1156
01:17:07,640 --> 01:17:09,799
to be right there with me.

1157
01:17:09,800 --> 01:17:12,919
I feel humbled in his presence.

1158
01:17:12,920 --> 01:17:16,119
From deep, deep in here,
ladies and gentlemen...

1159
01:17:16,120 --> 01:17:18,519
- let me lay on you...
- A great entertainer.

1160
01:17:18,520 --> 01:17:21,559
- A great entertainer...
- A great humanitarian.

1161
01:17:21,560 --> 01:17:25,039
- A great humanitarian...
- And my dear friend for 25 years.

1162
01:17:25,040 --> 01:17:27,519
And my dearest, dearest friend
for20years...

1163
01:17:27,520 --> 01:17:29,919
(CHUCKLES)
You missed by five years.

1164
01:17:29,920 --> 01:17:32,199
Oh, boy, do I hate show business.

1165
01:17:32,200 --> 01:17:34,319
Joey, you love show business.

1166
01:17:34,320 --> 01:17:38,047
That's right. I love show business.
I'll go either way.

1167
01:17:40,400 --> 01:17:43,285
- (♪ UP-TEMPO)
- (NO AUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

1168
01:17:49,960 --> 01:17:52,479
I got insight into you, Gideon.

1169
01:17:52,480 --> 01:17:54,679
You know what's underneath?

1170
01:17:54,680 --> 01:17:57,759
The dreadful fear
that you're ordinary...

1171
01:17:57,760 --> 01:17:59,759
not special.

1172
01:17:59,760 --> 01:18:01,883
Right.

1173
01:18:03,400 --> 01:18:06,999
(MOANING) I think...

1174
01:18:07,000 --> 01:18:08,999
I think...

1175
01:18:09,000 --> 01:18:10,799
I'm getting an erection.

1176
01:18:10,800 --> 01:18:14,402
Oh, Mr. Gideon, don't...
don't do that!

1177
01:18:14,760 --> 01:18:18,119
That sex thing... Jesus!

1178
01:18:18,120 --> 01:18:20,719
Listen, I wouldn't say
you were a faggot...

1179
01:18:20,720 --> 01:18:23,999
but you do have a lot
of feminine characteristics.

1180
01:18:24,000 --> 01:18:25,770
Right?

1181
01:18:28,720 --> 01:18:30,679
Right.

1182
01:18:30,680 --> 01:18:32,882
(♪ CONTINUES)

1183
01:18:37,520 --> 01:18:41,042
You are foolishly and childishly
flirting with disaster.

1184
01:18:41,880 --> 01:18:44,559
(WOMAN) Joe, what are you doing?

1185
01:18:44,560 --> 01:18:47,809
You're really crazy! What do
you want to do, kill yourself?

1186
01:18:50,960 --> 01:18:53,766
Dr. Ballinger told me
to get a little exercise.

1187
01:18:55,600 --> 01:18:59,239
Everything he does seems to be
a denial of his condition.

1188
01:18:59,240 --> 01:19:02,879
Dr. Ballinger, every time I've
seen him, I get the impression...

1189
01:19:02,880 --> 01:19:05,999
that he doesn't care
whether he lives or dies.

1190
01:19:06,000 --> 01:19:08,959
Yes, I know.
But I think he cares a lot.

1191
01:19:08,960 --> 01:19:11,919
Starting now, we'll limit his
visitors to no more than two.

1192
01:19:11,920 --> 01:19:14,319
(JOSH) Joe, I wish
you could have been there.

1193
01:19:14,320 --> 01:19:17,239
9:30 this morning, before a
single review was out...

1194
01:19:17,240 --> 01:19:20,239
the line at Cinema One
was around the block.

1195
01:19:20,240 --> 01:19:24,039
The people know.
I mean, the people know!

1196
01:19:24,040 --> 01:19:27,839
This broke every first-day record.
It's a blockbuster. A blockbuster.

1197
01:19:27,840 --> 01:19:31,359
I mean a blockbuster!

1198
01:19:31,360 --> 01:19:34,279
And those guys in California...

1199
01:19:34,280 --> 01:19:36,439
You wouldn't believe
the telephone calls.

1200
01:19:36,440 --> 01:19:40,199
"Congratulations," they say.
"We're glad you took your time.

1201
01:19:40,200 --> 01:19:42,479
It was worth it.

1202
01:19:42,480 --> 01:19:46,839
Every dollar we put in that film
is up there on the screen."

1203
01:19:46,840 --> 01:19:50,879
I'm telling you, they're talking about
a $ 3 1/2 million advertising budget.

1204
01:19:50,880 --> 01:19:53,199
Three and a half million dollars!

1205
01:19:53,200 --> 01:19:55,679
I'm sorry. Excuse me.
Do you believe that?

1206
01:19:55,680 --> 01:19:57,679
Three and a half million dollars!

1207
01:19:57,680 --> 01:20:00,039
This picture is going
right through the roof.

1208
01:20:00,040 --> 01:20:02,279
Right through...

1209
01:20:02,280 --> 01:20:03,959
the roof!

1210
01:20:03,960 --> 01:20:06,279
Look at those reviews.
See? We did it.

1211
01:20:06,280 --> 01:20:09,359
Joe, we did it!

1212
01:20:09,360 --> 01:20:11,479
Where are the bad ones?

1213
01:20:11,480 --> 01:20:13,839
There are no bad ones.

1214
01:20:13,840 --> 01:20:15,959
